      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (RH index) must be directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion and clinically relevant hemolysis endpoint.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the QoI specified in the FDA guidance for CPB device submissions. RH < 1 is the regulatory acceptance criterion. The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model used in CFD has been validated against in-vitro data for centrifugal pumps in multiple published studies. QoI relevance at gradation 2 is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same device geometry, blood analogue fluid, and operating range as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (identical to COU geometry), a 36 % glycerol-water blood analogue at matched viscosity, and the same five operating points defined in the COU. Geometric similarity, fluid similarity, and operating-point coverage are all confirmed. Validation relevance at gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
